original: Hultman, Sven Anders Gkleon, pastor, folkhögskoilliärare, Växjö, f. 8/5/09 i Månsarp, Jönköp. 1. G. 36 m. fil. kand. Barbro Hamrin. Barn: Ingrid f. 39, Sven-Gunnar 41, Lena 46. — Teol. kand. samt prästv. 33. Kommin. i Ramkvilia 36-45, lär. v. S:t Sigfrids folkhögsk. i Växjö sed. 42. Resor t. FinL, Norge, Danm., Tyskl. o. Ital. 30, 31 o. 37.
translated: Hultman, Sven Anders Gkleon, pastor, folk high school teacher, Växjö, born May 8, 1909 in Månsarp, Jönköping. Married once, in 1936 to Barbro Hamrin, who has a degree in philosophy. They have three children: Ingrid, born 1939, Sven-Gunnar, born 1941, and Lena, born 1946. Sven Anders Gkleon has a Bachelor of Theology degree and was ordained as a priest in 1933. He was a curate in Ramkvilia from 1936 to 1945, and a teacher at S:t Sigfrids folk high school in Växjö from 1942. He has traveled to Finland, Norway, Denmark, Germany, and Italy in 1930, 1931, and 1937.
